         <div type="apparatus">
            <p> Throughout JMR has underdotted more letters than C. and in l.1 JMR adds added <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">
                  <unclear reason="damage">Α</unclear>
               </foreign> after Marcus (raising the possibility of a Marcus Aurelius here) and at the end <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">Λ</foreign>, so <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">
                  <supplied reason="lost">βου</supplied>λήσεται</foreign> for C.'s <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">
                  <supplied reason="lost">βουλ</supplied>ήσεται</foreign>, in l.4 at the end <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">
                  <unclear reason="damage">Υ</unclear>
               </foreign>.</p>
